From: enfs-dkms
Subject: [PATCH] include/linux/sunrpc/sched.h: add RPC_TASK_ENFS (0x0008), stub RPC_TASK_FIXED

OpenEuler's enfs needs two RPC_TASK_* flag bits on rpc_task->tk_flags:
RPC_TASK_ENFS (was 0x0008 on OE 6.6) and RPC_TASK_FIXED (was 0x0040).

  - 0x0008 is still free in Ubuntu 7.0 → keep RPC_TASK_ENFS at 0x0008.
  - 0x0040 is now RPC_TASK_NETUNREACH_FATAL in 7.0. Every other bit
    0x0001-0x8000 in the 16-bit tk_flags field is also consumed.
    Widening tk_flags from `unsigned short` to `unsigned int` would
    shift every subsequent rpc_task field, breaking the CRC of every
    sunrpc export that mentions rpc_task (and so locking out
    unmodified lockd/nfs_acl/nfsd modules).

  - Compromise: stub RPC_TASK_FIXED to 0 (always-false). enfs's
    `task->tk_flags & RPC_TASK_FIXED` reads always evaluate false,
    so the "skip failover for fixed tasks" optimization is disabled.
    Base multipath dispatch + failover still work normally. The
    affected callers (pm_ping.c, failover_path.c) just lose a
    micro-optimization that pinned ping/probe tasks to their
    currently-selected xprt.

This file is consumed by both genksyms and gcc; #defines don't appear
in CRC computation, so the additions don't affect symbol versions and
no __GENKSYMS__ guard is needed.

---
--- a/include/linux/sunrpc/sched.h
+++ b/include/linux/sunrpc/sched.h
@@ -145,6 +145,22 @@
 #define RPC_TASK_NO_RETRANS_TIMEOUT	0x4000		/* wait forever for a reply */
 #define RPC_TASK_CRED_NOREF	0x8000		/* No refcount on the credential */
 
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_SUNRPC_ENFS)
+/* enfs: dispatched by the enfs subsystem (matches OE 6.6 bit). 0x0008
+ * is the only free bit in the 16-bit tk_flags field on Ubuntu 7.0 -
+ * every other position 0x0001-0x8000 is consumed (verified). */
+#define RPC_TASK_ENFS		0x0008
+/* RPC_TASK_FIXED - OE-specific "pin task to its current xprt" flag.
+ * OE 6.6 used 0x0040 which is now RPC_TASK_NETUNREACH_FATAL on 7.0.
+ * No other bit is free in tk_flags, and widening tk_flags shifts every
+ * subsequent struct field (CRC-breaking + KMI-breaking). We therefore
+ * stub RPC_TASK_FIXED to 0 (always-false) so enfs's "skip failover
+ * for fixed tasks" path becomes a no-op. Base multipath dispatch +
+ * failover still work; only the pin-to-current-xprt micro-optimization
+ * is lost. */
+#define RPC_TASK_FIXED		0
+#endif
+
 #define RPC_IS_ASYNC(t)		((t)->tk_flags & RPC_TASK_ASYNC)
 #define RPC_IS_SWAPPER(t)	((t)->tk_flags & RPC_TASK_SWAPPER)
 #define RPC_IS_SOFT(t)		((t)->tk_flags & (RPC_TASK_SOFT|RPC_TASK_TIMEOUT))
